---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import { site } from "../data/site";

const lastUpdated = "25 April 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`Terms of Use — ${site.name}`}
  description="Terms of use for the Ascend Griffin website and services."
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="legal">
    <div class="site-container legal-container">
      <header class="legal-header">
        <p class="legal-eyebrow">Legal Information</p>
        <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
        <p class="legal-meta">Effective from {lastUpdated} · {site.name} · {site.city}</p>
      </header>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>1. General Provisions</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms of Use govern the relationship between <strong>{site.name}</strong> (hereinafter —
          "the practice"), owned by sole proprietor (ФОП) {site.founder} ({site.city}, Ukraine), and visitors
          to the website <a href={site.url}>{site.domain}</a> and prospective clients of the practice.
        </p>
        <p>
          By using the Site or contacting us, you confirm that you have read these
          Terms and agree to them.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>2. Purpose of the Site</h2>
        <p>
          The website ascendgriffin.org is an informational resource of the practice. The information
          presented on the Site is for informational purposes only and <strong>does not constitute a public offer</strong>
          within the meaning of Article 641 of the Civil Code of Ukraine. Specific terms of collaboration are defined in
          an individual agreement or service contract.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>3. Intro Call (Free Consultation)</h2>
        <p>
          The first intro call, lasting up to 30 minutes, is provided free of charge and creates
          no obligations for either party. Its purpose is to discuss your context and
          determine whether we can be mutually useful.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>4. Paid Services</h2>
        <p>
          All paid services (Audit, Discovery, Recovery) are provided on the basis of
          an individual written agreement or service contract, which defines:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Scope of work and expected deliverables</li>
          <li>Timelines</li>
          <li>Cost and payment terms</li>
          <li>Guarantees and revision terms</li>
          <li>Terms for ending the collaboration</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Prices shown on the Site are indicative and may vary depending on the scope and
          complexity of the specific project.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>5. Guarantees and Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>The quality of the work</strong> (analysis, plan, documentation) is guaranteed
          within the scope of the signed agreement. If a deliverable does not meet the agreed requirements,
          revisions are made free of charge.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Business outcomes</strong> (sales growth, a successful product launch,
          fundraising, and so on) are not guaranteed, as they depend on many external
          factors: the market, competitors' actions, the client's management decisions, and general circumstances.
        </p>
        <p>
          The practice is not liable for:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Business decisions made by the client based on the recommendations provided</li>
          <li>Actions or inaction of third parties (contractors, vendors, suppliers)</li>
          <li>Changes in market conditions or legislation after a service is delivered</li>
          <li>Technical failures of third-party services (hosting, payment systems)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>6. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>The Site's content</strong> (texts, design, logos, brand) is the intellectual
          property of the practice. Its copying and distribution without written permission is prohibited.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Work deliverables</strong> (documentation, analyses, plans) created within the scope
          of a signed agreement transfer to the client's ownership after full payment, unless
          otherwise stipulated in the agreement.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Methodologies, templates, and internal tools</strong> used by the
          practice to carry out the work remain the intellectual property of Ascend Griffin
          and are not transferred to the client.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>7. Confidentiality</h2>
        <p>
          All information received from the client during the collaboration is confidential. Before
          any detailed discussion, we are ready to sign a mutual non-disclosure agreement (NDA).
          Details of personal data processing are set out in the
          <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>8. Payment Terms</h2>
        <p>
          All settlements for services rendered are made in accordance with the terms of the signed agreement.
          Standard terms are 50% prepayment and 50% upon completion of the work. Payment is made
          by bank transfer to the sole proprietor's (ФОП) bank account.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>9. Dispute Resolution</h2>
        <p>
          In the event of a dispute, the parties undertake to first resolve it through negotiation.
          If an agreement cannot be reached, the dispute is referred to the relevant judicial
          body at the contractor's place of registration ({site.city}, Ukraine) in accordance with the applicable
          laws of Ukraine.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>10. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to change these Terms. The current version is always published
          on this page with the date it was updated. Changes are not retroactive and do not affect
          agreements already concluded.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>11. Contact</h2>
        <ul class="contact-list">
          <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a></li>
          <li><strong>LinkedIn:</strong> <a href={site.linkedin} target="_blank" rel="noopener">linkedin.com/in/taras732</a></li>
          <li><strong>Address:</strong> {site.city}</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    padding: 80px 0 96px;
    min-height: 60vh;
    background: var(--bg-0);
  }
  .legal-container {
    max-width: 780px;
  }
  .legal-header {
    margin-bottom: 56px;
    padding-bottom: 32px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-1);
  }
  .legal-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent-pressed);
    margin: 0 0 12px;
  }
  .legal h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4.5vw, 44px);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: var(--text-1);
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }
  .legal-meta {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--text-3);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .legal-section {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }
  .legal h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    color: var(--text-1);
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }
  .legal p,
  .legal ul {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-2);
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }
  .legal ul {
    padding-left: 22px;
  }
  .legal li {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .legal strong {
    color: var(--text-1);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .legal a {
    color: var(--accent-pressed);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    transition: color var(--dur-fast) var(--ease);
  }
  .legal a:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .contact-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding-left: 0;
  }
  .contact-list li {
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
</style>
